title: For Sale:  Swedish M38 Mauser (96/38) For Sale
postcontent: I have a Carl Gustav Swedish M38 Mauser in 6.5x55 mm for sale. This particular gun was manufactured originally in 1916. This rifle started life as an M96 then the barrel was shortened from 29" to 24" as part of the conversion to a M38 rifle by Carl Gustav armorers. That would make this rifle technically an M96/38, but the Swedes did not distinguish between these converted rifles and the other M38s. These Swedish Mausers are known to be good accurate shooters, and the 6.5x55 round shoots flat and has low recoil. It is also easy to reload.This particular rifle shows a fair amount of wear on the exterior metal. The stock has some dings and nicks, but is in good overall condition. The bore is typical of these Swedish rifles with a good shine and nice rifling. The stock disks reads "0" which is the best possible condition. There is a discrete import mark on the bottom of the muzzle end of the barrel. The numbers match except for the butt plate and the front band (this may have been a miss-strike, since the number is 780 instead of 280). This rifle has one of the rare Vasteras rear sights. These sights were put on the rifle to compensate for the change in sighting with the shortening of the barrel. These sights alone sell for $100 to $150.I just noticed in the photos that this rifle is missing the front sight blade, which I removed to put on a taller one. I've got the sight blade around here somewhere, and will install it before the sale if I can find it. If not, I think a replacement is around $10.I'm asking $400 for the rifle. Sold "AS IS". I'm located in Winston Salem.Text me if interested at REDACTED. I have more photos available upon request.
